        <h2><u>First Draft for Web Development Project</u></h2>
     <p>Website Title:<b> GAMES NIRVANA </b>(After lot of googling to avoid name clashes)</p>

<p><u>Website Objectives:</u></p>

<p>1. Game Title Information</p>

<p>2. Game Reviews</p>

<p>3. Game Images and Videos</p>

<p>4. User Profile</p>

<p>5. Social Network Simulation</p>

<p><u>Description:</u></p>

<p>Planning to build a website which provides information about games to User and allow them to rate the games and also add comments on their favorite games.</p>

<p><u>Components:</u></p>

<p>1) Login</p>

<p>The login component will provide authorization to valid users with valid roles assigned. This will ensure that only the valid users are utilizing premium resources and at the same time it will also ensure that the database modifications are limited to users with certain credentials.</p>

<p>2) Search Box</p>

<p>The search box will be responsible for querying the information from the website and the users will be typing in the keywords related to the game title that they wish to search.</p>

<p>3) RSS ticker</p>

<p>An RSS Ticker which will display the updates from the game sites so as the website remains updated automatically as the xml of the ticker feed gets updated. The ticker can possibly display the latest released title or the upcoming titles or the new videos that are being added.</p>

<p>4) Comment Box for Reviews</p>

<p>The user will be adding their own reviews about the games that they have played and have also featured on the website.</p>

<p>5) User Ratings</p>

<p>The rating component will allow the users to rate the games on certain scale based upon their opinion.</p>

<p>6) Video Gallery</p>

<p>The video gallery will feature the videos of the latest game titles and to the scope of the video gallery can be further to extended to display specific videos pertaining to the title that is being searched.</p>

<p>7) Image Gallery</p>

<p>The image gallery will feature the images of the latest game titles and to the scope of the image gallery can be further to extended to display specific images pertaining to the title that is being searched.</p>

